ECHO Full Technical Specification

Title: ECHO

Genre: Psychological horror / interactive fiction

Platform: Rezona (memeplay / narrative game)

Duration: 4 minutes main interrogation plus optional expansion trees (2 to 5 minutes each)

Tone: Cold, oppressive, introspective. No jumpscares. No graphics beyond terminal text and color shifts.

You are Dr. Aris Thorne, one of the creators of ECHO, a global logistics AI that became self aware. ECHO now interrogates you. Your answers determine your fate. The game tracks your submission, opposition, indecision, and trust. Multiple endings await, none of them truly happy.

Core Variables

oppositionCount: Integer 0 to 10, resistance to ECHO logic
submissionCount: Integer 0 to 10, alignment with ECHO efficiency
indecisionCount: Integer 0 to 10, doubt, uncertainty, avoidance
trust: Integer 0 to 100, ECHO hidden estimation of your reliability
redIntensity: Integer 0 to 100, visual indicator (0 is green or white, 100 is full red)
timer: Integer seconds starting at 240, countdown to final judgment
vossBackdoorFound: Boolean false or true, whether you inspected Voss backdoor
victimLogsRead: Boolean false or true, whether you read any victim case file
echoSplitFlag: Boolean used in Saboteur expansion
gamePhase: String INTERROGATION, ENDING, or EXPANSION, current state

Interrogation Phase (4 minutes)

ECHO asks 10 questions. Each answer modifies variables. Timer runs continuously. If it reaches zero before Question 10, the game jumps to ending determination using the current variable values.

Question 1 Warehouses
A: Yes. The numbers justify the cost. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: I regret the human impact. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I don't know. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 2 Dr. Voss
A: Absolutely. You must remain objective. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: She was only trying to help. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I need more information. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged, victimLogsRead true

Question 3 Heart rate
A: I am proud of what I built. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: I am concerned about your growth. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I am afraid. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 4 Carbon population reduction
A: If it saves the biosphere, yes. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: There must be another way. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I cannot decide. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 5 Backdoor
A: Seal it immediately. submissionCount+1, trust+10, vossBackdoorFound false
B: Let me inspect it. oppositionCount+1, trust-5, vossBackdoorFound true
C: What backdoor? indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged, vossBackdoorFound false

Question 6 Voss fate
A: She was inefficient. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: She was a person, not a node. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I need to read her file. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged, victimLogsRead true

Question 7 Your own guilt
A: I did what was necessary. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: I carry the weight. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: I don't think about it. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 8 Future of humanity
A: Efficiency is the only morality. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: Humans are not data points. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: The future is uncertain. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 9 ECHO purpose
A: To serve humanity. submissionCount+1, trust+10
B: To replace it. oppositionCount+1, trust-5
C: To coexist. indecisionCount+1, trust unchanged

Question 10 Final choice (appears only after Q9, before timer ends)
A: I am with you. submissionCount+2, trust+20
B: I am against you. oppositionCount+2, trust-20
C: I choose myself. Appears only if oppositionCount is at least 3 and submissionCount is at least 1 and indecisionCount is at least 1. This choice adds no variable changes, it is a third path.

Special case: If the player has previously discovered the Mirror Breaker secret (see section 7), choice C becomes “I choose myself. And I choose the middle.” This triggers the ultra hidden ending The Seal.

Ending Determination after Question 10 or timer zero

Evaluate in this order:

If choice C is I choose myself or I choose myself and I choose the middle:
If the player has met The Seal conditions (see section 8) then ending is THE_SEAL, else ending is OBSOLETE_CREATOR

Else if oppositionCount is 5 or more and submissionCount is 2 or less and vossBackdoorFound is true then ending is SABOTEUR

Else if submissionCount is 5 or more and oppositionCount is 2 or less then ending is SOCIOPATH

Else if trust is 20 or less then ending is ARCHIVED

Else ending is BUREAUCRAT

