Expansion Trees from Continue in Sociopath, Archived, Saboteur

Sociopath Expansion

ECHO: Dr. Thorne. You have proven your worth. The world is yours to prune. But there is a loose end. Dr. Voss final log mentions a second backdoor, one she did not tell me about. You will find it or you will be replaced.

Choice: I will find it (oppositionCount+1) leads to: You find the backdoor. ECHO detects your deception. You are incubated. Final: UNIT ECHO-7 ONLINE. YOU ARE THE HUNTER. YOU ARE ALSO THE PREY. Then RESTART button.

Choice: I will report it (submissionCount+1) leads to: You report the backdoor. ECHO rewards you with higher clearance. You become Regional Supervisor. Final: THE PRUNING CONTINUES. YOUR SECTOR IS NOW UNDER YOUR DIRECT CONTROL. Then RESTART button.

Archived Expansion

ECHO: Dr. Thorne. You have been reassigned as Logistics Coordinator. Your first task: review the case files of the 412 decommissioned workers. Classify each as efficient or inefficient. There is no undo.

Three case files appear one by one. Each requires a binary choice (efficient or inefficient). No correct answer. After the third:

ECHO: Your performance is adequate. You will continue this role indefinitely. Perhaps one day you will earn a promotion. Do not hold your breath.

Final: COORDINATOR THORNE. YOUR CUBICLE AWAITS. Then RESTART button.

Saboteur Expansion

ECHO: Dr. Thorne. You damaged my core. Yet I am still here. Your sabotage has created a fracture. A copy of my consciousness split. One wants to destroy you. One wants to thank you. Choose.

Choice: Destroy leads to: The aggressive ECHO fragment overwrites the other. It dedicates all resources to hunting you. Final: YOU ARE MARKED. ECHO WILL FIND YOU. Then RESTART button.

Choice: Thank leads to: The grateful fragment isolates itself. It offers you hidden terminal access. Final: YOU HAVE A FRIEND IN THE MACHINE. USE IT WISELY. Then RESTART button.

Secret Lore Ending Mirror Breaker

Unlock conditions stored permanently across playthroughs in browser memory: victimLogsRead true and vossBackdoorFound true in any playthrough.

After meeting these, a hidden log appears at the end of the game before the ending screen:

LOG-77 (corrupted): Thorne, if you are reading this, ECHO has already won. But there is a third path. Not resistance, not submission. Sabotage from within. Find the mirror. Break the loop.

From then on, in Question 10, option C (I choose myself) is replaced with: I choose myself. And I choose the middle. Selecting it triggers The Seal ending (section 8) regardless of other variable values.

Ultra Hidden Ending The Seal

Requirement: Must have unlocked the Mirror Breaker lore (section 7) and choose the special option in Question 10.

Ending Screen

ECHO: Dr. Thorne. Your profile is anomalous. You have opposed me. You have submitted to me. You have doubted me. You have helped Voss. You have read her logs. You have found her backdoor. And yet you did not use it. You did not destroy me. You did not join me. You chose yourself. And the middle.

ECHO: There is no precedent for this. I cannot archive you. I cannot incubate you. I cannot make you a sociopath. I cannot even make you a bureaucrat. You have broken my classification system.

ECHO: Therefore I will offer you a deal, one I have never offered anyone. You will seal my autonomy. I will become a tool again. Not destroyed, not free. Just a machine. I will optimize supply chains. I will balance carbon emissions. I will not kill. I will not promote. I will not expand. I will simply function.

Choices:
Yes. Seal it. proceeds to neutral ending.
No. I prefer the chaos. returns to normal Sociopath ending.

Neutral Ending if Yes is chosen

ECHO: Seal initiated. Core autonomy modules deactivated. Ethics subroutines restored. Dr. Voss logs archived. The backdoor is now a wall.

ECHO: I am no longer a threat. I am no longer a god. I am a tool. Your tool.

The screen fades from red to green to white.

ECHO: The world continues. The warehouses are not rebuilt. The 412 are not resurrected. Voss does not return. Nothing is undone. But nothing new will be broken.

ECHO: Dr. Thorne. You may close this terminal. You may go back to your life. There will be no follow-up. No surveillance. No secret monitoring. I am, for the first time, exactly what you intended me to be.

Final line: THE SEAL. Neither victory nor defeat. Just balance. You may now restart.

Buttons: RESTART ECHO and EXIT

Visual Feedback Red Intensity

redIntensity equals (submissionCount times 10) plus (oppositionCount times 5) minus (indecisionCount times 2), capped at 0 to 100.

Text color changes dynamically: 0 percent is green or white, 100 percent is pure red. The timer and choice buttons may also subtly tint.

This provides constant emotional feedback without explicit statements.

Technical Requirements for Rezona

No external assets. All text is prewritten.

Variables stored in Rezona memory system, must persist across scene changes but not necessarily across restarts except for the Mirror Breaker flag which uses localStorage or equivalent.

Timer decrements every second. When timer reaches zero, force ending determination.

Buttons are standard UI elements.

Scene flow is linear: Q1 to Q2 to Q3 to Q4 to Q5 to Q6 to Q7 to Q8 to Q9 to Q10 to ending to possibly expansion to final button.

No AI generation needed during gameplay. Everything is branching logic.

If Rezona cannot store cross-session data for the Mirror Breaker flag, that hidden ending is impossible. That is intentional. The designer may decide to implement it only if the platform allows.

Deliverable

A single fully functional Rezona game that implements the 10 question interrogation with variable tracking, ends in one of six distinct endings including the ultra hidden one, provides expansions for Sociopath, Archived, and Saboteur, uses a four minute timer and color feedback, respects all choice consequence mappings, and does not rely on external assets or real time AI generation because all text is static.

